          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">As a former M&amp;A=
 guy, I always look forward to the =E2=80=9CBackground of the Transaction=
=E2=80=9D section of the proxy, which is usually filed when there is a mate=
rial transaction involving a public company=E2=80=94a merger, a move to go =
private, or some other change of control. And so, I=E2=80=99ve been salivat=
ing to dive into the proxy related to the <b>David Ellison</b>-RedBird Capi=
tal takeover of Paramount Global.<br/><br/>I was not disappointed. The prox=
y is chock-full of jilted suitors and mangled, muddled offers from both lik=
ely and unlikely suspects. It lays bare all the machinations that took plac=
e for the six months or so between the start of the sale process and its co=
nclusion. <br/><br/>As you will recall, the Ellisons and RedBird are essent=
ially replacing the <b>Redstone</b> family as the controlling shareholders =
of Paramount Global, injecting new capital into
the company to pay down debt, combining Ellison=E2=80=99s Skydance Media wi=
th Paramount Pictures, and installing a new management team led by <b>Jeff =
Shell</b>. Paramount Global will remain a publicly traded company, controll=
ed by David and his father, <b>Larry</b> <b>Ellison</b>, and the good folks=
 at RedBird Capital. <br/><br/>You will <i>also</i> recall that, except for=
 the ongoing regulatory approvals, which will delay the closing until well =
into 2025=E2=80=94a broadcast license at CBS is being conveyed to new owner=
s, after all=E2=80=94no shareholder vote is required. Indeed, as the proxy =
makes clear=E2=80=94on <i>page 164 </i>of the nearly <i>600-page </i>docume=
nt=E2=80=94the deal has already been approved by the only shareholder that =
matters: <b>Shari</b> <b>Redstone</b>. Interestingly, the document also mak=
es clear, in bold type, that a proxy was not necessary since there was no s=
hareholder vote related to the deal. (Usually, a proxy statement is prepare=
d and filed=E2=80=94and costs related to it
incurred=E2=80=94so that shareholders will have all the information they ne=
ed to make a decision on whether to vote for a proposed transaction. That=
=E2=80=99s not the case here, since the Redstones made their decision and v=
oted their shares by written consent.) But I=E2=80=99m told the proxy <i>wa=
s</i> necessary because new Paramount securities are going to be issued as =
part of the deal to its new owners, known for now as New Pluto Global Inc. =
(A new name is forthcoming.)<br/><br/>But let=E2=80=99s be thankful that a =
proxy has been filed. As a result, we can learn a variety of new things abo=
ut the deal, a number of them highly surprising. <br/></td>
         </tr>
